1
00:00:48,580 --> 00:00:52,980
[The Ferry Man: 10th Anniversary]

2
00:00:53,410 --> 00:00:55,890
[Episode 5]

3
00:00:56,810 --> 00:01:00,350
[My dear princess, did you sleep well?]
[Yuanji]

4
00:01:03,110 --> 00:01:05,000
Yuanji, my dear husband.

5
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:11,150
Hold on.

6
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:13,600
I want to go take a shower first.

7
00:01:22,710 --> 00:01:23,710
Don't go.

8
00:01:25,950 --> 00:01:27,350
Stay with me a bit longer.

9
00:01:29,070 --> 00:01:29,870
Give me a kiss,

10
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,120
okay?

11
00:01:32,710 --> 00:01:33,310
Wang Fang?

12
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,120
You fell asleep again.

13
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,450
And you didn't even eat.

14
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,700
I have no appetite.

15
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,479
Your dark circles

16
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:43,080
are as heavy as a panda's.

17
00:01:43,430 --> 00:01:45,289
Didn't you sleep well last night?

18
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:46,729
Did you

19
00:01:46,780 --> 00:01:47,640
do something bad in your dream

20
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,640
with that husband of yours, Yuanji?

21
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,570
Good afternoon,

22
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:55,479
my princess.

23
00:01:56,789 --> 00:01:58,870
So sweet. "My princess."

24
00:01:59,640 --> 00:02:00,570
Oh my god.

25
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:01,730
If only Yuanji

26
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:02,430
could say that to me.

27
00:02:02,020 --> 00:02:04,160
[Director]

28
00:02:02,710 --> 00:02:03,940
That must cost a lot of money.

29
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:04,630
Exactly.

30
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:05,310
Yeah.

31
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:07,400
Director.

32
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,120
Now?

33
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,890
Okay, I'll be right there.

34
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:16,280
I don't even look like myself now.

35
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:18,840
It's the "blue enchantress" look.
You look pretty.

36
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:20,280
The last video

37
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,190
got 700,000 likes.

38
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:22,910
Yan Yuzhen's traffic is dropping.

39
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,710
We need to do something about it.

40
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,120
Most of

41
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:27,630
her fans are male,

42
00:02:28,079 --> 00:02:30,120
and they get bored very easily.

43
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:33,150
Posting videos of dancing
in front of peonies every day—

44
00:02:33,150 --> 00:02:33,910
no matter how beautiful you are,

45
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,910
they'll eventually get tired of it.

46
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:45,110
Men are always like that.

47
00:02:45,190 --> 00:02:46,650
It's the same everywhere.

48
00:02:51,520 --> 00:02:52,400
Let's shoot a few videos

49
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,060
with this makeup look as well.

50
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:55,400
Wang Fang, you write the script.

51
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,750
Don't always copy and paste from AI.

52
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:58,410
Add some of your own thoughts.

53
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:07,550
Although my appearance

54
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:08,150
filled the blank

55
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,400
in your life,

56
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:10,470
buying me dinner

57
00:03:10,470 --> 00:03:11,710
is a bit too fancy.

58
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,760
There's no need for this.

59
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,030
Don't worry, you don't have to pay.

60
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:16,960
That's a relief.

61
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,030
This is the table Ms. Huang reserved,

62
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:24,030
but she hasn't arrived yet.

63
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:24,910
Please wait here for a moment, gentlemen.

64
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:25,510
Thank you.

65
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,450
Okay, thank you.

66
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,079
Hello.

67
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,530
This way, Ms. Huang.

68
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:47,800
Ms. Huang.

69
00:03:48,870 --> 00:03:49,870
I'm Xia Dongqing.

70
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:52,000
Hello, I'm Huang Shang.

71
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:52,680
Hello.

72
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,170
Why are there two of you?

73
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,700
This... This is my friend,

74
00:03:56,710 --> 00:03:57,510
Zhao Hengzhi.

75
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:58,150
Hello.

76
00:03:58,190 --> 00:03:58,850
Have a seat.

77
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:03,420
I already ordered.

78
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:04,560
Surely you two grown men

79
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:05,870
don't have any
dietary restrictions, right?

80
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:06,630
I don't eat...

81
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:07,090
Hold on.

82
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:08,570
Cilantro...

83
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:09,520
I don't eat garlic.

84
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:09,870
I...

85
00:04:09,870 --> 00:04:10,730
Useless bunch.

86
00:04:11,050 --> 00:04:11,680
It's been 3 months,

87
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,030
and you still can't get it done?

88
00:04:13,030 --> 00:04:13,960
I've heard enough. Save it.

89
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,280
Hand in your resignation this afternoon.

90
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,040
Pardon her.

91
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:18,560
My daughter has always been like this.

92
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:20,360
Work comes before everything else,

93
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,160
and her temper

94
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:23,120
is even worse than her workaholic nature.

95
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:24,310
Please don't take it to heart.

96
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:25,720
That's why her love life

97
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,410
has been put on hold until now?

98
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,160
Yes.

99
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,270
For a woman, instead of struggling so hard

100
00:04:31,270 --> 00:04:32,510
to earn so much money,

101
00:04:33,050 --> 00:04:34,400
wouldn't it be better

102
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:36,159
to have someone who understands
and cares for her?

103
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,120
Don't you agree?

104
00:04:38,430 --> 00:04:40,090
That's not necessarily true.

105
00:04:41,120 --> 00:04:42,690
Is this a blind date?

106
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:43,600
In your dreams.

107
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:46,390
The dishes have been served.

108
00:04:46,390 --> 00:04:47,520
Let's start eating.

109
00:04:49,650 --> 00:04:50,390
I'm not worried

110
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,510
that you're scammers.

111
00:04:51,510 --> 00:04:53,640
At worst, you just scam me out of a meal.

112
00:04:54,250 --> 00:04:54,840
Anyway,

113
00:04:54,870 --> 00:04:57,200
I haven't been to this place
in a long time.

114
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:58,240
These were all my favorite dishes

115
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,170
when I was young.

116
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,160
So,

117
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:03,560
what did my mother,
who passed away 2 years ago,

118
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,820
ask you to tell me?

119
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,650
"After thousands of years of evolution,

120
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:17,600
women have become wiser,

121
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:18,680
more elegant,

122
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:20,050
and more powerful.

123
00:05:20,630 --> 00:05:22,070
They are the Athenas walking through

124
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,750
the concrete jungle."

125
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:25,460
This copy is good.

126
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:26,770
What woman

127
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:28,130
would want to be Athena?

128
00:05:28,740 --> 00:05:29,870
If there's a choice,

129
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:32,240
of course we'd rather be Yan Yuzhen.

130
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,680
It's too objectifying toward women—

131
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,870
reducing everything to
romance and indulgent pleasure.

132
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:36,600
Yan Yuzhen is

133
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,070
quite similar to

134
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:39,040
Marie Antoinette.

135
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,510
Neither of them ended well.

136
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:42,840
They were both the epitome of femininity—

137
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:45,560
beautiful, wealthy, enjoying life,

138
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:47,480
and backed by powerful men.

139
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,240
Seriously,

140
00:05:48,530 --> 00:05:49,290
what woman

141
00:05:49,630 --> 00:05:51,159
wouldn't want that kind of life?

142
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:51,920
Nonsense.

143
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:53,300
Your view is

144
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:54,480
too male-centric.

145
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,720
Yan Yuzhen's fans

146
00:05:55,720 --> 00:05:56,630
are also male.

147
00:05:57,210 --> 00:05:58,730
We need to get female fans.

148
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:00,680
She who wins female fans wins the world.

149
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:01,430
I agree.

150
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:04,090
All the gifts from destiny

151
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:05,160
have secretly

152
00:06:05,190 --> 00:06:06,070
been priced.

153
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,480
Relying on men has never been

154
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,070
a good thing for women.

155
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:12,390
Why should I get married?

156
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:13,790
If you don't get married,

157
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:14,680
your mom won't be able to

158
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,480
rest in peace.

159
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:17,330
Easy for you to say.

160
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,830
Who am I supposed to marry?

161
00:06:18,830 --> 00:06:20,430
I've got no time for a boyfriend.

162
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:22,000
I'm swamped every single day.

163
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,270
At least you have friends, right?

164
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:24,190
You can ask your friends

165
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:25,720
to introduce you to someone.

166
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,920
I don't have friends.

167
00:06:27,210 --> 00:06:28,090
In business,

168
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,890
there are only opponents and allies.

169
00:06:29,890 --> 00:06:30,920
And depending on the circumstances,

170
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,250
those roles can change.

171
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,290
Are you married?

172
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:38,650
He's not.

173
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:39,510
I'm not.

174
00:06:39,920 --> 00:06:41,320
You don't look annoying.

175
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:42,310
Do you have a girlfriend?

176
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:42,800
No.

177
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:44,870
I guess not, right?

178
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:45,530
No, I don't.

179
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,140
Occupation?

180
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:46,770
Teacher.

181
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:47,510
College professor.

182
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:48,440
Full professor.

183
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,580
Ask my mom what she thinks.

184
00:06:53,190 --> 00:06:54,720
Actually, you're pretty decent.

185
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,560
Your occupation

186
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,360
is quite nice,

187
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,890
and you look like a good guy.

188
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,770
Why don't you try dating first?

189
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:01,390
Well...

190
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,600
Your mom said

191
00:07:02,830 --> 00:07:04,330
you two could try dating first.

192
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:06,060
I don't have time to try dating.

193
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:07,280
My mom's demand

194
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:08,510
is for me to get married.

195
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:09,510
Then what are we waiting for?

196
00:07:09,510 --> 00:07:10,710
Why not make it quick?

197
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:12,830
That won't work. We haven't even...

198
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:13,960
You're not willing?

199
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:16,950
How do I look?

200
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:17,930
Beautiful.

201
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,190
Really beautiful.

202
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:19,920
My company

203
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:21,210
develops real estate,

204
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,340
and I'm the CEO.

205
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:23,830
In every first-tier city,

206
00:07:23,830 --> 00:07:24,870
I have properties.

207
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:25,390
So,

208
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,930
are you satisfied with my conditions?

209
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,070
I am.

210
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:33,430
Marrying her would be like
getting a city thrown in with the deal.

211
00:07:34,510 --> 00:07:36,510
My mom is sitting right here, right?

212
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:42,600
Mom.

213
00:07:42,909 --> 00:07:44,280
I'm beautiful and rich,

214
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:45,600
and I'm doing perfectly fine on my own.

215
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,070
Why would I need a boyfriend?

216
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,430
To come and share the fruits
of my success?

217
00:07:48,430 --> 00:07:49,430
But you can't just

218
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:51,080
be alone for your whole life.

219
00:07:51,190 --> 00:07:52,850
It's not like I refuse to date.

220
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:54,870
I wouldn't mind having a baby,

221
00:07:54,870 --> 00:07:57,310
but I'd rather keep the child
and leave the father out of the picture.

222
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,270
That won't do.

223
00:08:04,190 --> 00:08:05,480
I have to get back to the company.

224
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:06,210
So annoying.

225
00:08:06,390 --> 00:08:07,590
You guys keep eating.

226
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:08,480
I...

227
00:08:12,750 --> 00:08:13,880
Tell my mom to relax.

228
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,030
Instead of stressing over
pointless things,

229
00:08:16,030 --> 00:08:18,430
she should wish me success
with my project.

230
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,920
If she's still worried,

231
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,710
I'll just burn her

232
00:08:20,710 --> 00:08:22,630
a son-in-law as an offering in a few days.

233
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:23,360
I'm leaving.

234
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:31,190
Madam, please don't be anxious.

235
00:08:31,190 --> 00:08:32,720
Rushing things won't help.

236
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:33,630
Marriage

237
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,870
indeed depends on fate.

238
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,630
Actually,

239
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:41,549
there's something else
I want to talk to her about.

240
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:46,340
But she won't listen.

241
00:08:50,150 --> 00:08:50,750
Director,

242
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,270
see you at the office tomorrow.

243
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,530
Okay. Good work today.

244
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:57,240
Ya, you've worked hard today too.

245
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:59,040
What do you want to eat? My treat.

246
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:00,400
There's no one watching the café today.

247
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,510
I want to wait for Dongqing to come back,

248
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:03,170
so we can make a few more sales.

249
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:05,750
Ya,

250
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,450
you've got a pimple.

251
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:17,040
How can a Heavenly Maiden get pimples?

252
00:09:17,270 --> 00:09:18,320
Have you noticed

253
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,840
that your strength

254
00:09:19,870 --> 00:09:21,930
is getting weaker and weaker lately?

255
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:29,320
That's because you've been human
for too long.

256
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,330
Your body

257
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,420
is gradually turning into a human's.

258
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:35,680
In ancient times,

259
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:38,020
300 Chang'es came to the human world.

260
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:39,390
But now,

261
00:09:39,630 --> 00:09:41,390
not a single surviving Heavenly Maiden

262
00:09:41,390 --> 00:09:43,190
can be found in the mortal world.

263
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,070
According to Kunlun,

264
00:09:46,870 --> 00:09:49,030
if a Heavenly Maiden lives with humans,

265
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:50,150
she'll fall ill.

266
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:55,990
But never being able to return to Kunlun

267
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,270
isn't truly a punishment,

268
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:04,790
It's because they

269
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,440
have all become humans—

270
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,510
weak, short-lived humans.

271
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:12,270
You will age,

272
00:10:12,870 --> 00:10:13,750
get sick,

273
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,390
wither,

274
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,080
die,

275
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:18,870
and vanish.

276
00:10:20,150 --> 00:10:22,080
You will become an ordinary woman.

277
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:25,000
Are you willing to accept that?

278
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,670
I don't know.

279
00:10:30,550 --> 00:10:31,910
I'll become a human?

280
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,000
This

281
00:10:35,390 --> 00:10:37,450
is the consequence of pursuing love.

282
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:40,240
Love is a palace built by humanity,

283
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,180
decorated with

284
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:42,990
language,

285
00:10:43,410 --> 00:10:43,950
literature,

286
00:10:43,950 --> 00:10:44,870
and art.

287
00:10:46,030 --> 00:10:49,360
It's magnificent and breathtaking,
dazzling beyond measure,

288
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,690
drawing people to it
like moths to a flame.

289
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,440
People pour their hearts and souls
into entering it,

290
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:55,270
only to find

291
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,520
that inside lies

292
00:10:57,550 --> 00:10:59,200
an even more brutal forest.

293
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:03,030
There, people battle one another
in the name of love.

294
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:03,790
Beauty,

295
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:04,960
wealth,

296
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:06,250
manipulation—

297
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:09,960
these are the weapons of lovers.

298
00:11:12,440 --> 00:11:13,480
Congratulations,

299
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,550
my dear princess.

300
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:17,440
Your Affection Level
has reached 1 million.

301
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:18,510
Please make your choice:

302
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:20,970
would you like to summon Yuanji
to your side?

303
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:34,200
What am I thinking?

304
00:11:38,030 --> 00:11:39,480
Those with weak weapons—

305
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,550
especially women—

306
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:45,000
are often the victims in love.

307
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:47,390
Be careful.

308
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:49,750
In the forest of love,

309
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:53,360
smiling beasts lie in wait.

310
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:57,240
Wait,

311
00:11:57,630 --> 00:12:00,030
why could her mother appear
during the day?

312
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:01,750
What's so strange?

313
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,120
Huang Shang's attitude

314
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,120
was very strange.

315
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:05,150
If an ordinary person found out

316
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:06,910
their mother's spirit was there,

317
00:12:06,910 --> 00:12:08,150
they wouldn't react like that, would they?

318
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:09,480
She's the strange kind.

319
00:12:09,860 --> 00:12:10,440
You can tell at a glance she's not

320
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:11,500
the ordinary type.

321
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:13,830
You're right.

322
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:15,600
Could it be like

323
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,850
the situation with Dapeng last time?

324
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,240
My wife's calling me.

325
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,170
I'll hang up now.

326
00:12:30,630 --> 00:12:31,150
Honey.

327
00:12:31,390 --> 00:12:33,120
Why didn't you turn on the lights?

328
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,120
There was no one in the café,

329
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,580
so I forgot to turn them on.

330
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:36,790
I've been running around all day.

331
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,600
I'm so tired.

332
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,640
What did you do today?

333
00:12:39,910 --> 00:12:41,390
First, I went to run some errands

334
00:12:41,390 --> 00:12:42,450
with Zhao Hengzhi.

335
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:43,810
After we finished,

336
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,150
I went with him to the market
to pick out fish.

337
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:48,410
Zhao Hengzhi really likes keeping fish.

338
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:49,870
Then,

339
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,870
I drove him back to school.

340
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:53,440
We bumped into 2 acquaintances

341
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,440
who insisted on playing ping-pong.

342
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,770
Don't look at other men.

343
00:13:19,030 --> 00:13:20,030
I'll get jealous.

344
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,860
You're exactly the way

345
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,650
I imagined you in my dreams.

346
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:29,480
Then your dream has come true,

347
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,210
my princess.

348
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:33,250
By getting my Affection Level
up to 1 million,

349
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:34,600
would my game character

350
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:35,960
really come to me?

351
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:42,510
You're not

352
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,090
dreaming right now.

353
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,330
I spent money on you in the game—

354
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,630
a lot of money—

355
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:50,870
just to get our Affection Level
to 1 million.

356
00:13:50,870 --> 00:13:51,550
Thank you.

357
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,320
But that's not what matters.

358
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:59,430
What matters is your love for me.

359
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:03,000
Will you

360
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,360
disappear tomorrow?

361
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:06,880
That depends on you,

362
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,150
my princess.

363
00:14:08,910 --> 00:14:09,870
If you wish,

364
00:14:10,940 --> 00:14:12,390
I'll stay by your side forever.

365
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:13,720
Stay by my side forever?

366
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:18,600
Do I need to keep topping up?

367
00:14:19,030 --> 00:14:20,090
You have to believe

368
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,000
that there are miracles in life.

369
00:14:23,550 --> 00:14:24,240
Money

370
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,030
can create miracles.

371
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,400
The choice is yours.

372
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,120
Then,

373
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:38,420
are you willing to do anything for me?

374
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:39,960
That's a promise.

375
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,480
I want a diamond ring.

376
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:42,840
Can you

377
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,100
give it to me tomorrow?

378
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:56,280
Y-You already had it prepared?

379
00:15:02,870 --> 00:15:03,510
However,

380
00:15:04,910 --> 00:15:05,910
keeping the ring

381
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,400
comes with a small price.

382
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,480
What price?

383
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,560
Stay with me tonight,

384
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,230
okay?

385
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:17,720
Let's do everything

386
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,650
we did in the game

387
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:19,870
all over again.

388
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:49,440
Let's go, baby.

389
00:15:53,270 --> 00:15:55,390
I didn't expect it to integrate so well.

390
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:56,790
It can be used right away.

391
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:17,460
[Chapter 4: Strange Things]

392
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,270
Be careful

393
00:16:27,630 --> 00:16:28,890
when you go take a leak.

394
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:31,070
Don't go bumping into anything.

395
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:32,750
This town isn't very big,

396
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:34,750
but once it gets dark,
every house is empty.

397
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:35,790
With just the two of us here,

398
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:36,920
it's really creepy.

399
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,670
This place has been here
for hundreds of years.

400
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,930
Who knows how many people have died here.

401
00:16:43,080 --> 00:16:44,340
What are you afraid of?

402
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:48,080
I've been in property development
for so many years,

403
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,340
and I'll tell you this—

404
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:51,210
there's no place in this world

405
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:53,130
where people haven't died.

406
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,060
According to the records,

407
00:16:59,120 --> 00:16:59,980
there should be

408
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,320
another well nearby.

409
00:17:01,870 --> 00:17:03,530
Let's go take a look tomorrow.

410
00:17:11,270 --> 00:17:12,270
It smells so good.

411
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,060
What's that smell?

412
00:17:16,349 --> 00:17:17,880
It smells like cosmetics.

413
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:41,760
Watch out!

414
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:53,080
♪ Green willows cover my boudoir ♪

415
00:17:53,820 --> 00:17:58,560
♪ I adorn myself before the mirror ♪

416
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:05,080
♪ I put on a red dress every day ♪

417
00:18:05,690 --> 00:18:11,710
♪ Year after year,
my love never comes home ♪

418
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:18,950
♪ In the yellow earth mound,
I shall lie alone ♪

419
00:18:19,450 --> 00:18:26,490
♪ When will the grass turn green again? ♪

420
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,720
Ghosts!

